1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:00:58,150 --> 00:01:04,340
[Running Like A Shooting Star]

3
00:01:11,330 --> 00:01:12,289
I'm fine.

4
00:01:14,150 --> 00:01:15,880
There's no need to surround me.

5
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:21,210
[Episode 9: Enter Your Own Peak State]

6
00:01:17,590 --> 00:01:18,720
It's an old problem.

7
00:01:19,539 --> 00:01:20,800
What's wrong with you?

8
00:01:21,070 --> 00:01:21,990
Old problem.

9
00:01:21,990 --> 00:01:23,270
What old problem?

10
00:01:23,340 --> 00:01:24,140
Ms. Luo,

11
00:01:24,270 --> 00:01:25,310
take a look at him.

12
00:01:25,820 --> 00:01:27,470
There are many types of doctors.

13
00:01:27,470 --> 00:01:29,330
I specialize in Sports Medicine.

14
00:01:30,460 --> 00:01:32,120
Given his current condition,

15
00:01:32,180 --> 00:01:34,440
it's difficult for me to make a judgment.

16
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:38,930
How long have you

17
00:01:39,660 --> 00:01:41,060
been experiencing this?

18
00:01:43,740 --> 00:01:44,830
Answer him.

19
00:01:44,830 --> 00:01:45,960
How long has it been?

20
00:01:47,670 --> 00:01:48,670
Actually,

21
00:01:50,550 --> 00:01:52,229
it started in my second year of high school.

22
00:01:52,229 --> 00:01:53,140
At first,

23
00:01:54,630 --> 00:01:55,800
my coach thought

24
00:01:55,830 --> 00:01:58,490
it was just vomiting due to excessive training.

25
00:02:00,860 --> 00:02:02,990
But the situation worsened over time.

26
00:02:04,940 --> 00:02:07,340
When my talent for running was discovered,

27
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:09,610
I began high-intensity training.

28
00:02:10,419 --> 00:02:11,950
Honestly,

29
00:02:11,950 --> 00:02:12,950
I enjoy training.

30
00:02:13,670 --> 00:02:14,770
I also understand that people around me

31
00:02:14,770 --> 00:02:16,770
have very high expectations for me.

32
00:02:16,829 --> 00:02:18,670
But the higher the expectations,

33
00:02:18,670 --> 00:02:20,390
the greater the disappointment.

34
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:23,590
During a city-level Youth Track and Field Championship,

35
00:02:23,820 --> 00:02:25,790
everyone thought I could win,

36
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,570
but unexpectedly,

37
00:02:27,820 --> 00:02:29,150
Liu Haoyu emerged.

38
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:31,550
You'll have to try harder

39
00:02:32,060 --> 00:02:33,690
if you want to surpass me, a genius.

40
00:02:33,690 --> 00:02:35,220
Qi Tian is nothing special.

41
00:02:36,010 --> 00:02:37,420
What genius?

42
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:39,500
I think he's just not up to it.

43
00:02:43,950 --> 00:02:44,750
Later on,

44
00:02:45,470 --> 00:02:48,000
my coach always used Liu Haoyu to motivate me.

45
00:02:48,010 --> 00:02:49,090
What's funny is,

46
00:02:49,700 --> 00:02:51,360
nowadays when I see Liu Haoyu,

47
00:02:51,710 --> 00:02:53,550
he doesn't even remember me.

48
00:02:54,310 --> 00:02:55,990
Maybe I'm just lame.

49
00:02:56,020 --> 00:02:58,060
You can't even bear this little suffering.

50
00:02:58,060 --> 00:02:59,070
You think having a bit of talent

51
00:02:59,070 --> 00:03:00,710
makes you extraordinary, huh?

52
00:03:00,710 --> 00:03:01,950
Look at Liu Haoyu.

53
00:03:03,220 --> 00:03:04,170
I was training

54
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,160
while vomiting.

55
00:03:05,700 --> 00:03:06,940
I swore that I'll beat Liu Haoyu

56
00:03:06,940 --> 00:03:09,060
at the next High School Games.

57
00:03:09,510 --> 00:03:12,030
During this time, the thing with Shen Ming happened.

58
00:03:12,030 --> 00:03:12,910
In a fit of pique,

59
00:03:12,910 --> 00:03:15,240
he left and kept training with his father.

60
00:03:15,630 --> 00:03:18,230
So he didn't know about my training condition.

61
00:03:18,390 --> 00:03:19,810
Why is it that I work so hard,

62
00:03:19,810 --> 00:03:21,710
yet you can breeze through effortlessly?

63
00:03:21,710 --> 00:03:23,100
You've always been the supporting character in my life,

64
00:03:23,100 --> 00:03:24,329
the one who always lagged behind.

65
00:03:24,329 --> 00:03:26,990
But now, you've become the school's superstar.

66
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:33,579
My parents also boasted to everyone,

67
00:03:33,860 --> 00:03:36,260
saying that a running genius had emerged in our family

68
00:03:36,260 --> 00:03:39,680
and that they would organize a group to watch me in the Olympics in the future.

69
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:40,920
They had no idea

70
00:03:41,690 --> 00:03:44,290
that I was light-years away from the Olympics.

71
00:03:44,950 --> 00:03:47,210
All of this added immense pressure on me.

72
00:03:47,690 --> 00:03:48,420
Eventually,

73
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:51,130
my weight dropped to 55 kilogram.

74
00:03:51,790 --> 00:03:53,550
How can you call yourself a man if you can't even bear this little suffering?

75
00:03:53,550 --> 00:03:54,350
Why are you kneeling there?

76
00:03:54,350 --> 00:03:55,150
What a loser.

77
00:03:55,150 --> 00:03:56,270
Weak-kneed.

78
00:04:12,830 --> 00:04:13,740
Meaningless.

79
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:15,850
So meaningless.

80
00:04:16,620 --> 00:04:17,570
It's so boring.

81
00:04:20,589 --> 00:04:22,850
My body seemed to have reached its limit.

82
00:04:24,660 --> 00:04:25,740
For a while,

83
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:29,830
just the thought of running

84
00:04:32,060 --> 00:04:33,430
made me nauseous,

85
00:04:34,980 --> 00:04:36,110
and seeing training

86
00:04:37,870 --> 00:04:39,870
made me physically uncomfortable.

87
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,220
God gave me ankles suited for running,

88
00:04:45,430 --> 00:04:46,700
but didn't give me

89
00:04:47,030 --> 00:04:48,420
a matching body.

90
00:04:57,150 --> 00:04:58,740
I'm probably just a joke.

91
00:05:14,150 --> 00:05:15,090
No,

92
00:05:15,670 --> 00:05:17,000
you're not a joke.

93
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:20,540
I will help you get better.

94
00:05:23,630 --> 00:05:24,470
Sir.

95
00:05:27,340 --> 00:05:29,070
It's just that you have too much empathy,

96
00:05:29,070 --> 00:05:30,130
competitiveness,

97
00:05:30,590 --> 00:05:32,320
and sense of responsibility.

98
00:05:32,730 --> 00:05:34,740
Trust me. You will get better.

99
00:05:35,300 --> 00:05:38,110
Running and food don't make you vomit.

100
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,430
The real reason for your vomiting

101
00:05:40,580 --> 00:05:42,020
is the mental stress

102
00:05:42,110 --> 00:05:43,230
that has disrupted

103
00:05:43,700 --> 00:05:45,590
your digestive system.

104
00:05:46,260 --> 00:05:49,820
Mental stress can cause sympathetic nervous system imbalance,

105
00:05:49,820 --> 00:05:51,630
autonomic nervous system disorder,

106
00:05:51,630 --> 00:05:53,630
gastric acid secretion imbalance,

107
00:05:53,750 --> 00:05:56,750
and insufficient blood supply to the gastric mucosa.

108
00:05:57,150 --> 00:05:59,480
This has long been confirmed in medicine.

109
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:04,120
Actually,

110
00:06:05,180 --> 00:06:08,050
I've noticed for a while that you might have

111
00:06:08,810 --> 00:06:10,180
mental stress issues.

112
00:06:13,830 --> 00:06:15,590
You always think about

113
00:06:15,950 --> 00:06:17,230
how to train harder.

114
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:21,440
But you never think about stopping yourself.

115
00:06:22,910 --> 00:06:24,310
In the disdain of others,

116
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:27,360
in self-denial,

117
00:06:29,470 --> 00:06:31,000
you keep pushing yourself.

118
00:06:32,820 --> 00:06:33,630
Eventually,

119
00:06:34,340 --> 00:06:36,070
both physically and mentally,

120
00:06:37,300 --> 00:06:39,230
you fall into endless exhaustion.

121
00:06:41,390 --> 00:06:43,520
But once the exhaustion accumulates,

122
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,110
one...

123
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:48,030
loses their radiance.

124
00:06:50,620 --> 00:06:52,550
If it weren't your own experience,

125
00:06:53,150 --> 00:06:55,010
how could nineteen-year-old you

126
00:06:55,270 --> 00:06:57,260
speak such words?

127
00:07:00,830 --> 00:07:01,630
Xue Yiran,

128
00:07:02,740 --> 00:07:04,340
help Qi Tian back to rest.

129
00:07:05,940 --> 00:07:07,520
As for tomorrow's final...

130
00:07:08,990 --> 00:07:09,700
Fatty.

131
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:10,710
You go.

132
00:07:11,180 --> 00:07:12,420
Me？

133
00:07:17,460 --> 00:07:18,270
Fatty.

134
00:07:19,380 --> 00:07:20,180
I'm sorry.

135
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:24,420
I held everyone back.

136
00:07:26,030 --> 00:07:27,360
I disappointed you all.

137
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:28,380
Qi Tian,

138
00:07:29,110 --> 00:07:30,910
stop being overly responsible.

139
00:07:31,230 --> 00:07:32,580
Originally, we didn't count on you

140
00:07:32,580 --> 00:07:33,980
to compete in this match.

141
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:36,110
Didn't you hear what Wang said?

142
00:07:36,110 --> 00:07:38,510
Hurry up and become an irresponsible jerk.

143
00:07:40,830 --> 00:07:43,580
[Changing Room]

144
00:07:52,540 --> 00:07:54,370
You're such a jinx.

145
00:07:54,430 --> 00:07:56,010
You even dropped the baton.

146
00:07:57,470 --> 00:07:59,409
It's said that during the second leg baton exchange of Huainan,

147
00:07:59,409 --> 00:08:01,190
the runner went out of the exchange zone.

148
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:03,650
As a result, Huainan's result was declared invalid

149
00:08:03,650 --> 00:08:04,650
and canceled.

150
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:21,540
♫Don't want to be afraid. I hurt to hesitate♫

151
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:28,370
♫But we can't wait to feel this change♫

152
00:08:29,130 --> 00:08:32,570
♫It's not too late, free from hate♫

153
00:08:32,590 --> 00:08:38,750
♫Think of the future that we can crate. Face the facts today♫

154
00:08:38,770 --> 00:08:41,490
♫There's a better way♫

155
00:08:42,270 --> 00:08:43,270
The weather has been getting cold.

156
00:08:42,340 --> 00:08:48,340
♫Like a tree♫

157
00:08:46,380 --> 00:08:47,790
Why can you always find me

158
00:08:48,110 --> 00:08:49,240
no matter where I am?

159
00:08:52,150 --> 00:08:53,300
Aren't you curious

160
00:08:53,430 --> 00:08:55,180
about what place we came in yesterday

161
00:08:55,180 --> 00:08:56,240
with Fatty's help?

162
00:08:56,860 --> 00:08:57,940
What place?

163
00:08:59,070 --> 00:08:59,900
The fifth place.

164
00:08:59,900 --> 00:09:01,030
Impressive, right?

165
00:09:01,190 --> 00:09:03,070
We, and Fatty,

166
00:09:03,150 --> 00:09:04,750
came fifth in the whole city.

167
00:09:05,550 --> 00:09:06,230
Yesterday,

168
00:09:06,390 --> 00:09:08,860
Liu Haoyu didn't get to see you.

169
00:09:09,060 --> 00:09:10,840
He said we at Xinghe looked down on him,

170
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:12,500
making him race with a fat guy.

171
00:09:15,180 --> 00:09:15,980
Is that so?

172
00:09:16,820 --> 00:09:17,870
Obviously,

173
00:09:17,990 --> 00:09:19,180
Liu Haoyu

174
00:09:19,780 --> 00:09:22,180
has set his sights on you, the Golden Hound.

175
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:29,550
Your passive,

176
00:09:29,790 --> 00:09:30,740
non-rejecting,

177
00:09:31,380 --> 00:09:32,710
non-responsible state

178
00:09:33,110 --> 00:09:35,240
is starting to resemble that of a jerk.

179
00:09:39,740 --> 00:09:41,820
Coach told me to think less

180
00:09:42,300 --> 00:09:43,360
and daydream more.

181
00:09:45,390 --> 00:09:46,450
Speaking of Coach,

182
00:09:47,140 --> 00:09:49,390
Wang said he arranged a training camp in the mountains.

183
00:09:49,390 --> 00:09:51,050
It'll be at the end of October.

184
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:52,870
It's quite cold in the mountains.

185
00:09:52,870 --> 00:09:54,310
Would you like me to accompany you, Mr. Rustic,

186
00:09:54,310 --> 00:09:55,710
to buy some warm clothes?

187
00:10:02,790 --> 00:10:03,790
Do you think...

188
00:10:06,190 --> 00:10:07,870
Wang can really cure me?

189
00:10:08,830 --> 00:10:09,820
I don't know.

190
00:10:10,510 --> 00:10:11,350
He said so.

191
00:10:11,670 --> 00:10:12,930
Let's just believe it.

192
00:10:13,420 --> 00:10:15,820
Anyway, things won't get any worse for you.

193
00:10:25,870 --> 00:10:27,270
I want to believe in Wang.

194
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:35,360
If it weren't for you,

195
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:38,650
I don't think I could come back to running.

196
00:10:46,380 --> 00:10:47,180
Maybe

197
00:10:48,660 --> 00:10:50,500
I'd never be able to experience

198
00:10:50,610 --> 00:10:53,070
the heat of the sun reflecting off the track,

199
00:10:53,660 --> 00:10:55,520
smell the fragrance of the grass,

200
00:10:56,060 --> 00:10:57,990
or hear the cheers around me again.

201
00:10:58,410 --> 00:11:00,940
Every element of the track-and-field ground

202
00:11:01,110 --> 00:11:03,280
fills my heart with something.

203
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:07,500
I want to come back.

204
00:11:09,030 --> 00:11:10,200
I want to run again

205
00:11:10,540 --> 00:11:11,540
with full vigor.

206
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:14,560
Thank you, Xue Yiran.

207
00:11:25,770 --> 00:11:26,600
Actually,

208
00:11:27,760 --> 00:11:29,080
I just want to comfort

209
00:11:29,190 --> 00:11:31,250
the you from the past, full of wounds.

210
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:33,360
How great it would be

211
00:11:35,610 --> 00:11:37,270
if I could return to the arena.

212
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:01,430
I'm exhausted.

213
00:12:04,430 --> 00:12:06,030
In this Track and Field Club,

214
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:08,490
there's one with a hand injury,

215
00:12:08,490 --> 00:12:10,290
one frequently feels nauseous,

216
00:12:10,310 --> 00:12:11,990
and an old man about to retire.

217
00:12:12,980 --> 00:12:15,260
It's simply a team of the elderly and infirm.

218
00:12:15,260 --> 00:12:16,060
Ai Ziji,

219
00:12:16,750 --> 00:12:18,750
what's with your sarcasm

220
00:12:18,860 --> 00:12:19,900
every day?

221
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:25,030
The booked room isn't very professional.

222
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:27,610
It's just an ordinary guesthouse.

223
00:12:27,710 --> 00:12:30,020
So, we need to bring more equipment with us

224
00:12:30,020 --> 00:12:31,550
in case there isn't enough.

225
00:12:33,730 --> 00:12:35,890
Where's Wu Tianfu at a time like this?

226
00:12:36,470 --> 00:12:38,470
It's just me and Xue Yiran, two handsome guys,

227
00:12:38,470 --> 00:12:39,530
doing all the work.

228
00:12:39,810 --> 00:12:40,940
Is this reasonable?

229
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:44,100
I'm not very pleased

230
00:12:44,660 --> 00:12:47,520
with being on the same level as you in terms of looks.

231
00:12:47,550 --> 00:12:48,780
As the saying goes,

232
00:12:49,140 --> 00:12:51,110
"One should not be arrogant.

233
00:12:52,100 --> 00:12:52,900
Xue Yiran,

234
00:12:53,030 --> 00:12:54,070
who exactly

235
00:12:54,070 --> 00:12:55,330
do you think highly of?

236
00:12:55,550 --> 00:12:56,640
Go ahead and keep being arrogant.

237
00:12:56,640 --> 00:12:58,500
One day, you'll end up like Amumu.

238
00:13:02,230 --> 00:13:04,110
You even have the face to say that to me?

239
00:13:04,110 --> 00:13:05,030
Who,

240
00:13:05,430 --> 00:13:07,560
back in freshman year, had no friends,

241
00:13:07,580 --> 00:13:09,790
and was always moping in the corner with a sullen face,

242
00:13:09,790 --> 00:13:11,200
and blaming others for bullying you?

243
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:12,930
Xue Yiran, are you asking for a beating?

244
00:13:12,930 --> 00:13:14,760
Alright. Stop it, you two.

245
00:13:15,370 --> 00:13:17,590
Wu Tianfu said he went to Huainan University

246
00:13:17,590 --> 00:13:18,730
to have a meal with a friend.

247
00:13:18,730 --> 00:13:19,790
He'll be back soon.

248
00:13:21,310 --> 00:13:22,750
Look at Wu Tianfu.

249
00:13:23,060 --> 00:13:25,190
He made friends all the way to Huainan.

250
00:13:29,160 --> 00:13:31,360
Which friend of Wu Tianfu is in Huainan?

251
00:13:33,270 --> 00:13:33,750
Here.

252
00:13:33,770 --> 00:13:34,310
Here.

253
00:13:40,900 --> 00:13:42,580
Actually, I saw you that day.

254
00:13:42,860 --> 00:13:44,800
It's just that Qi Tian wasn't feeling well,

255
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:46,060
so I didn't come to you.

256
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:50,660
I didn't expect you to still remember it.

257
00:13:51,580 --> 00:13:52,310
It's fine.

258
00:13:52,670 --> 00:13:53,470
I'm used to it.

259
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:56,960
As a jinx,

260
00:13:58,230 --> 00:13:59,560
I can't do anything well

261
00:13:59,700 --> 00:14:00,580
except

262
00:14:01,350 --> 00:14:02,350
handle pressure.

263
00:14:06,460 --> 00:14:07,620
So what happened later?

264
00:14:07,620 --> 00:14:09,220
Did they give you a hard time?

265
00:14:09,850 --> 00:14:11,800
What else could they do to give me a hard time?

266
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:14,000
They just won't let me run in the future.

267
00:14:14,590 --> 00:14:15,350
Handing over the baton

268
00:14:15,350 --> 00:14:17,510
is something that requires two people.

269
00:14:17,510 --> 00:14:19,500
Why did they only target you?

270
00:14:20,510 --> 00:14:21,110
Tianfu,

271
00:14:22,420 --> 00:14:25,550
there isn't always a reason for everything in the world.

272
00:14:25,820 --> 00:14:27,350
We can only accept our fate.

273
00:14:29,580 --> 00:14:30,510
Who can I blame for the fact

274
00:14:30,510 --> 00:14:32,440
that I always seem to have bad luck?

275
00:14:45,300 --> 00:14:46,110
No.

276
00:14:46,580 --> 00:14:47,980
No, I don't agree with it.

277
00:14:48,140 --> 00:14:49,340
In my values,

278
00:14:49,540 --> 00:14:51,640
as long as you are willing to work hard,

279
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:54,240
there will definitely be results and rewards.

280
00:14:56,390 --> 00:14:58,050
That's because you're lucky.

281
00:15:00,230 --> 00:15:02,540
All the people in the world who work hard and get rewarded

282
00:15:02,540 --> 00:15:03,440
are lucky.

283
00:15:06,540 --> 00:15:07,910
Sometimes I wonder

284
